CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 20, 1957, pg. A3, reads: "Chief Council Chair - Aided by City Hall Superintendent Martin McTighe, Raymond Wharton, the city's only upholsterer, returns the council president's chair which he had refurbished. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh city upholsterer Raymond Wharton and City Hall superintendent Martin McTighe carrying Pittsburgh City Council president's chair, in council chambers
